Grizzly bears in areas surrounding Yellowstone National Park would be removed from the endangered species list under a proposal, officials said.
Fish and Wildlife Service is preparing to remove Yellowstone's grizzly bears from the endangered species list later this year.
Federal wildlife officials estimate that more than 600 grizzly bears now live in the region.
Chris Servheen, grizzly bear recovery coordinator for the Fish and Wildlife Service, said he also supported taking bears off the list.
The Bush administration on Tuesday is to take the first step toward removing Yellowstone's grizzly bears from the nation's endangered species list.
